# Introduction

This is a minimal example document that includes a glossary.

```{r setup, include=FALSE}
# Load necessary libraries
library(tidyverse)
library(flextable)

# Create sample data
glossary <- data.frame(
  Term = c("ADLs", "Alexithymia", "Asperger's Syndrome"),
  Definition = c(
    "Activities of Daily Living: Basic personal activities essential for health and safety.",
    "The inability to recognize or describe feelings.",
    "A part of autism spectrum disorder characterized by difficulty in social interaction."
  )
)
```

# Glossary

This section provides definitions for terms used in this document.

```{r, echo=FALSE}
# Create and print the flextable object
ft_glossary <- flextable(glossary) %>%
  theme_booktabs() %>%
  bold(part = "header") %>%
  fontsize(size = 12, part = "header") %>%
  font(part = "header", fontname = "Times") %>%
  bg(part = "header", bg = "grey") %>%
  fontsize(size = 10, part = "body") %>%
  font(part = "body", fontname = "Arial") %>%
  width(j = 1, width = 2.5, unit = "in") %>%
  width(j = 2, width = 5.5, unit = "in") %>%
  valign(valign = "top", part = "all")

# Print the flextable object
ft_glossary
```
